# Practice Module — Comprehensive Code Audit

> Based purely on source code analysis of every file in `app/lab/practice/` (28 files, ~5,500 lines of component code + 3,007-line data sheet).

---

## Part 1: What This Module Is Trying To Do

The Practice module is a **DSA (Data Structures & Algorithms) problem tracker and learning platform** living at `/lab/practice`. It's built around a 450+ problem sheet that spans 8 coding platforms (LeetCode, GFG, InterviewBit, CSES, CodeForces, SPOJ, LintCode, HackerEarth) organized by topic (Arrays, Recursion, Sorting, Linked Lists, etc.).

The module has **four interconnected modes**, each serving a different learning workflow:

### The Four Modes

```mermaid
graph LR
    B["Browse<br/><small>Discovery & tracking</small>"] -->|Focus button on row| F["Focus<br/><small>Deep work session</small>"]
    B -->|Swords button on row| I["Interview<br/><small>AI mock interview</small>"]
    B -->|Click problem| D["Drawer<br/><small>Attempt history overlay</small>"]
    F -->|After solve/quit| B
    A["Analyze<br/><small>Performance dashboard</small>"] -->|Focus button| F
    A -->|Interview topic button| I
    A -->|Review All button| B
    I -->|Report: View Analytics| A
    I -->|Report: Open in Browse| D
```

---

## Part 2: Component-by-Component Breakdown

### Infrastructure Layer

| File | Lines | Purpose | What It Actually Does |
