## Part 4: Issues Found

### 🔴 Critical Bugs

#### 1. "Try Again" button does nothing after giving up
**File:** [FocusView.tsx L89-101](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/components/focus/FocusView.tsx#L89-L101)

**What it's supposed to do:** After a user gives up on a problem in Focus mode, show a "Try Again" button that restarts the same problem.

**What actually happens:** The handler calls `setCompletedState(null)` which clears the "What's next?" screen, but the URL still has `?p=<problemId>`. However, because the `FocusCard` component is keyed by `problem.id` and React doesn't re-mount a component with the same key, the timer and form state are **NOT** reset. The user gets dumped back to the same card with their previous state intact. Worse, if `setCompletedState(null)` triggers while the URL is cleared, they land on `FocusEmpty` instead.

```tsx
onClick={() => {
  setCompletedState(null);
  // Missing: timer.reset(); timer.start();
  // Or: router.push(`/lab/practice/focus?p=${problemId}`)
}}
```

---

#### 2. React Rules of Hooks violation in InterviewReport
**File:** [InterviewReport.tsx L75-83](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/components/interview/InterviewReport.tsx#L75-L83)

**What it's supposed to do:** Optionally use `usePracticeContext()` to get the `openDrawer` function, so the "Open in Browse" button works. The try/catch is there because the code anticipates the component might be rendered outside `PracticeProvider`.

**What actually happens:** `require()` at render-time in a `"use client"` component bypasses the module bundler, and calling `usePracticeContext()` inside a try/catch violates React's Rules of Hooks (hooks must be called unconditionally and in the same order every render). In practice this "works" because the component is always inside `PracticeProvider`, but it's a ticking bomb — any refactor that moves it outside will crash React's hook reconciliation.

**Proper fix:** Just call `usePracticeContext()` normally. If it needs to work outside the provider, make the hook optionally return null instead of throwing.

---

#### 3. Status value mismatch between FocusCard and ProblemDrawer
**Files:** [FocusCard.tsx L53-57](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/components/focus/FocusCard.tsx#L53-L57), [ProblemDrawer.tsx L46](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/components/ProblemDrawer.tsx#L46)

**What it's supposed to do:** Both FocusCard and ProblemDrawer create attempts via the same `/api/attempts` endpoint.

**What actually happens:** ProblemDrawer's Attempt type declares `status: "attempting" | "resolved" | "solved_with_help" | "gave_up"` and sends `"attempting"` for initial creation + `"resolved"` or `"gave_up"` on reflection. FocusCard skips the `"attempting"` phase and sends `"resolved"` or `"gave_up"` directly. There's a TODO comment acknowledging this. The confusion means: if the API validates strictly, FocusCard attempts may fail; if it's lenient, the data is inconsistent (some attempts have the `attempting → resolved` lifecycle, others skip straight to `resolved`).

---

#### 4. Hardcoded mock message ignores selected problem/topic
**File:** [ActiveInterview.tsx L43-53](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/components/interview/ActiveInterview.tsx#L43-L53)

**What it's supposed to do:** Show the AI's first question about the selected problem.

**What actually happens:** The initial `messages` state always contains: *"You're given an array of meeting intervals [start, end]. Find the minimum number of conference rooms required."* — regardless of what topic, difficulty, or problem the user selected. If the API returns session messages, they replace this via `setMessages(loaded)`, but if the session has no messages yet (which is the common case for a newly-created session), the user sees the hardcoded meeting-rooms question.

---

#### 5. Hardcoded comparison string in ProgressCard
**File:** [ProgressCard.tsx L104](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/components/browse/ProgressCard.tsx#L104)

**What it's supposed to do:** Show how many problems were solved last week for comparison.

**What actually happens:** It always shows `(was 3)` — a hardcoded string that never updates. The `weeklyDelta` is fetched from the API but there's no corresponding "last week's value" field.

---

### 🟡 Architectural Gaps

#### 6. ProblemDrawer is a 1,534-line god component
**File:** [ProblemDrawer.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/components/ProblemDrawer.tsx)

**What it's trying to be:** A "mini-app" that shows everything about a problem — details, attempt history with CRUD, discussion threads, and an AI-powered "Explain" feature.

**The problem:** It manages ~20 pieces of state with `useState`, implements its own timer, reimplements code input and difficulty dots instead of using shared components, handles 5 API endpoints, has a reflection modal inlined as conditional JSX, and contains a 30-line markdown template generator for "VS Code export". Changing one feature risks breaking others. No sub-components are extracted — everything from the backdrop click handler to the discussion comment form is in one file.

---

#### 7. PracticeContext is too thin — modes don't share runtime state
**File:** [PracticeContext.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/context/PracticeContext.tsx)

**What it's supposed to do:** Be the shared state layer for all Practice modes.

**What it actually provides:** Static problem data (`SHEET` + `problemIndex` Map) and drawer state (`activeDrawer`, `openDrawer`, `closeDrawer`).

**What's missing:** 
- `savedProblems` and `completedProblems` — fetched from `useAuth()` independently in `BrowseView` and `FocusEmpty`
- `extensionMap` (attempt summaries) — fetched only in `BrowseView`, unavailable in other modes
- Filter state — lives in `useProblemFilters` hook (useState), lost on navigate away
- Active problem state for Focus mode — encoded in URL only, no context awareness

**Consequence:** When the user switches from Browse to Focus and back, all fetched data is discarded and re-fetched. `BrowseView` doesn't know what Focus just solved. Filters reset on every Browse → Focus → Browse trip.

---

#### 8. `isCompleted` field defined but never populated or read
**File:** [sheet.ts L10](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/data/sheet.ts#L10)

The `DSAProblem` interface has `isCompleted?: boolean` but:
- None of the 450+ problems in the SHEET set this field
- No code reads `problem.isCompleted`
- Completion is tracked via `user.completedProblems: string[]` from the auth context

This is dead code in the type definition — either a leftover from an earlier design or a planned feature that was superseded.

---

#### 9. Silent error swallowing in 10+ fetch calls
Every API call in the module uses this pattern:
```tsx
fetch(url)
  .then(res => res.json())
  .then(data => { /* set state */ })
  .catch(() => { }); // empty catch
```

**Found in:** `BrowseView` (×2), `FocusEmpty`, `TodaysFocus`, `InterviewManager`, `AnalyzeDashboard`, `ActiveInterview` (×2), `InterviewReport`. The user sees loading spinners that stop spinning but never learns what went wrong. No toast, no retry, no error state. `FocusCard` is the only component that shows an error message on save failure.

---

### 🟠 Duplication & DRY Violations

#### 10. Random problem picker duplicated 3 times
The exact same algorithm — "filter to unsolved problems → if none, use all → pick random" — appears in:
1. [BrowseView.tsx L92-98](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/components/browse/BrowseView.tsx#L92-L98) — for Search bar's "Pick Random"
2. [FocusEmpty.tsx L53-59](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/components/focus/FocusEmpty.tsx#L53-L59) — for "Pick Random Problem" button
3. [FocusEmpty.tsx L61-69](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/components/focus/FocusEmpty.tsx#L61-L69) — variant: "Next Review Problem" (picks from completed)

All three also independently compute `SHEET.flatMap(t => t.problems)` instead of using `problemIndex` from context.

---

#### 11. Difficulty color map defined in 3 different ways
The "Easy=green, Medium=yellow, Hard=red" color mapping:
- **ProblemRow lines 76-86:** inline `if` chain returning Tailwind class strings
- **FocusCard lines 22-27:** `DIFFICULTY_COLORS` Record object
- **ProblemDrawer:** inline in tag rendering (yet another copy)

These use slightly different class strings and approaches. A single `import { DIFFICULTY_COLORS } from "@/lib/constants"` would eliminate all three.

---

#### 12. Timer implemented 3 times
- **`useTimer` hook (52 lines):** Clean, well-structured hook with `useRef` for interval, `useCallback` for controls, `useMemo` for formatting. Used by Focus mode.
- **ProblemDrawer (lines 104-133):** Reimplements the same logic with inline `useState` + `setInterval` + `useEffect`. Adds auto-start when `showNewAttempt` toggles.
- **ActiveInterview (lines 79-88):** Another inline reimplementation with `elapsedSeconds`, `isRunning`, and `setInterval`.

Both reimplementations lack the cleanup safety that `useTimer`'s `useRef` provides and don't offer pause/resume/toggle.

---

#### 13. `SHEET.flatMap()` computed redundantly
The pattern `SHEET.flatMap((t) => t.problems)` appears in:
- `BrowseView` (line 55) — stored as `allProblems`
- `FocusEmpty` (line 33) — stored as `allProblems`
- `InterviewSetup` (line 47) — for topic list generation
- Potentially `TodaysFocus` (via suggestions API)

The context already has `problemIndex: Map<string, DSAProblem>` which indexes all problems. Components could use `Array.from(problemIndex.values())` or the context could expose a pre-computed flat array.

---

#### 14. Language dropdown options inconsistent between shared and inline
- **`CodeBlock.tsx`** (shared component): `["Python", "JavaScript", "TypeScript", "Java", "C++", "Go", "Other"]`
- **`ProblemDrawer.tsx`** (inline): `["Python", "JavaScript", "Java", "C++", "Go", "Other"]` — missing TypeScript

---

### 🔵 UX / Product Gaps

#### 15. Interview mode ignores `?p=` and `?topic=` URL params
**Impact:** Two cross-mode links are broken:
- `ProblemRow` has a Swords icon button navigating to `/lab/practice/interview?p=arr-5` — but `InterviewSetup` never reads `searchParams`, so the user arrives at a blank setup form
- `AnalyzeDashboard` has "Interview This Topic" linking to `/lab/practice/interview?topic=Trees` — same issue, topic is ignored

**What should happen:** `InterviewSetup` should pre-select the topic and/or pre-load the problem from URL params.

---

#### 16. Past interview sessions are displayed but not interactive
**File:** [InterviewSetup.tsx L237-265](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/components/interview/InterviewSetup.tsx#L237-L265)

Each past session `<div>` has `cursor-pointer` and `hover:bg-muted/30` styling — it **looks** clickable — but there's no `onClick` handler. Users can't:
- View the report of a past session
- Resume an in-progress session
- Re-run a completed session with the same config

---

#### 17. Phase transitions in interview are purely cosmetic
**File:** [ActiveInterview.tsx L320-357](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/components/interview/ActiveInterview.tsx#L320-L357)

The interview has 4 phases: Understanding → Approach → Code → Review. Phase buttons update `setPhase(...)` locally, which changes the button label and the "Phase: X" label in the header. But **the phase change is never communicated to the AI interviewer**. The `sendToApi()` function has a `"phase-change"` type available, but it's never called when the user clicks phase buttons. The AI continues with the same behavior regardless of what phase the user declares.

---

#### 18. Analyze → Browse "Review All" link uses non-functional filter param
**File:** [AnalyzeDashboard.tsx L317](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/components/analyze/AnalyzeDashboard.tsx#L317)

```tsx
router.push('/lab/practice?filter=Unresolved')
```

Browse mode's `page.tsx` doesn't read URL query params. The `useProblemFilters` hook initializes all filters from `useState("All")` — it never checks `searchParams`. So this link navigates to Browse but the "Unresolved" filter is silently ignored. The user sees all problems.

---

#### 19. "Load in VS Code" is actually a file download
**File:** [ProblemDrawer.tsx L437-470](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/components/ProblemDrawer.tsx#L437-L470)

**What the button says:** "Load in VS Code" with a FileText icon.

**What it does:** Creates a Blob with markdown content (title, platform, URL, description, tags, empty solution/notes sections), creates a download link, triggers `a.click()`, cleans up.

**What the user expects:** The problem opens in VS Code. Maybe via `vscode://` URI scheme or a VS Code extension API.

---

#### 20. No mobile responsiveness for Focus/Interview modes
- **Interview:** Chat area uses `px-12` fixed padding, input bar has `pb-20` for bottom spacing — on mobile, text is squeezed
- **Focus:** Card is `max-w-3xl` but approach/code textareas are fixed-height with no responsive adjustments
- **Browse** is the only mode that handles mobile via `hidden md:flex` on the sidebar, but even there the TopicSidebar is fixed-position with `pr-6` that could overlap content on narrow screens

---

#### 21. FocusEmpty "Next Review Problem" picks randomly from completed, not truly spaced
**File:** [FocusEmpty.tsx L61-69](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/components/focus/FocusEmpty.tsx#L61-L69)

**What the button says:** "↻ Next Review Problem" with a teal RotateCcw icon — implying spaced-repetition review.

**What it does:** `Math.random()` from all completed problems. There's no spaced repetition logic — no intervals, no scheduling, no "review due" checking. The `extensionMap` has a `reviewDue` field that *could* power this, but it's not used here. Meanwhile, `useProblemFilters` has a "Due for Review" status filter, and `ProblemRow` shows a teal refresh icon when `reviewDue` is true — but none of this connects to the Focus mode's review picker.

---

### 🟣 Data Model & Performance Concerns

#### 22. 124KB static data file shipped to every client
**File:** [sheet.ts](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/xandar-lab/app/lab/practice/data/sheet.ts) — 3,007 lines, 124KB

This file is imported by at least 5 client components (`BrowseView`, `FocusEmpty`, `InterviewSetup`, `TopicSidebar`, `PracticeContext`). Since they're all `"use client"`, this entire 124KB is bundled into the client JavaScript. For comparison, the sum of all *other* Practice module files is ~35KB.

Possible approaches: make the SHEET available via an API route, use React Server Components for the data injection layer, or code-split the data and load lazily.

---

#### 23. Problem tags conflate three different concerns
Tags like `["Dynamic Programming", "Easy"]` or `["Backtracking", "DFS", "Medium"]` are flat arrays that mix:
- **Difficulty:** Easy, Medium, Hard (used by filters, color coding, stats)
- **Algorithm/Pattern:** Two Pointers, DP, Sliding Window, etc. (used for topic display)
- **Meta:** Theory, Classic, Imp (informational labels)

Every consumer parses these differently:
- `BrowseView`: `p.tags?.includes("Easy")` — brittle string match
- `useProblemFilters`: `t.toLowerCase() === difficultyFilter.toLowerCase()` — case-insensitive compare
- `FocusCard`: `problem.tags?.find(t => ["Easy","Medium","Hard"].includes(t))` — first-match find
- `ProblemRow`: inline `if (tag === "Easy")` chain

A structured model like `{ difficulty: "Easy", patterns: ["DP", "Two Pointers"], meta: ["Classic"] }` would eliminate all this parsing.

---

#### 24. Platform filter only covers 3 of 8 defined platforms
**Types:** `Platform = 'LeetCode' | 'GeeksForGeeks' | 'InterviewBit' | 'LintCode' | 'CodeForces' | 'SPOJ' | 'CSES' | 'HackerEarth' | 'Other'`

**Filter UI:** Only offers LeetCode, GeeksForGeeks, and Other. This means InterviewBit problems (14 in the sheet), CSES problems, CodeForces problems, etc. all get lumped into "Other" — users can't filter by these specific platforms.

---

## Part 5: Data Flow Diagram

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Auth Context (global)"
        AC["useAuth()<br/>user.savedProblems[]<br/>user.completedProblems[]"]
    end

    subgraph "Practice Context"
        PC["PracticeProvider<br/>SHEET (static)<br/>problemIndex Map<br/>activeDrawer state"]
    end

    subgraph "Browse Mode"
        BV["BrowseView"] -->|fetches| API1["/api/attempts/summary"]
        BV -->|fetches| API2["/api/analytics/activity"]
        BV -->|reads| AC
        BV -->|uses| PF["useProblemFilters hook<br/>(local state only)"]
        BV --> TF["TodaysFocus"] -->|fetches| API3["/api/suggestions"]
        BV --> PL["ProblemList → ProblemRow"]
        BV --> PC2["ProgressCard"]
        BV --> FP["FilterPanel"]
        PL -->|save/complete| API4["/api/problems/save"]
        PL -->|save/complete| API5["/api/problems/complete"]
    end

    subgraph "Focus Mode"
        FV["FocusView"] -->|reads ?p= param| FC["FocusCard"]
        FV -->|no param| FE["FocusEmpty"]
        FC -->|POST| API6["/api/attempts"]
        FE -->|fetches| API3
        FE -->|reads| AC
    end

    subgraph "Analyze Mode"
        AD["AnalyzeDashboard"] -->|fetches| API7["/api/analytics?range="]
        AD -->|openDrawer| PC
        AD -->|links to| FV
        AD -->|links to| IM
    end

    subgraph "Interview Mode"
        IM["InterviewManager"] -->|fetches/creates| API8["/api/interviews"]
        IM --> IS["InterviewSetup"]
        IM --> AI2["ActiveInterview"] -->|sends messages| API9["/api/interviews/{id}/message"]
        AI2 -->|ends session| API10["/api/interviews/{id}"]
        IM --> IR["InterviewReport"] -->|fetches| API10
        IR -->|saves attempt| API6
    end

    subgraph "Drawer (cross-mode)"
        DO["DrawerOverlay"] -->|reads| PC
        DO --> PD["ProblemDrawer (1534 lines)"]
        PD -->|fetches| API6
        PD -->|fetches| API11["/api/attempts/discussions"]
        PD -->|fetches| API12["/api/explanations"]
    end

    PC -->|used by| BV
    PC -->|used by| FV
    PC -->|used by| AD
    PC -->|used by| TF
    PC -->|used by| DO
```

